{% set failed_intents = '' %}
{% for intent in json.loads(intents) %}
    {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n# Intent name: " ~ intent.name ~ " (" ~ intent.working_hours_state ~ ") " %}
    {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n## CTA Status:" %}
    {% if intent.assessment is defined and intent.assessment.cta is defined %}
        {% if intent.assessment.cta.completed %}
            {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ " ✅ COMPLETED" %}
        {% else %}
            {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ " ❌ NOT_COMPLETED" %}
        {% endif %}
        {% if intent.assessment.cta.agent_goal is defined %}
            {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n- Goal: " ~ intent.assessment.cta.agent_goal %}
        {% endif %}
        {% if intent.assessment.cta.assessment is defined %}
            {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n- Notes: " ~ intent.assessment.cta.assessment %}
        {% endif %}
    {% else %}
        {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ " ⚠️ MISSING" %}
    {% endif %}

    {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n## Auditor instruction:\n" ~ intent.auditor_instruction %}

    {% if intent.outcome is defined %}
        {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n## Expected outcome:\n" ~ intent.outcome %}
    {% endif %}

    {% if intent.channel is defined %}
        {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n## Channel: **" ~ intent.channel ~ "**" %}
    {% endif %}
    {% if intent.checklist is defined %}
        {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n## Checklist:" %}

        {% for item in intent.checklist %}
            {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n- " ~ item %}
        {% endfor %}
    {% endif %}

    {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n## Step results:" %}
    {% if intent.assessment is defined and intent.assessment.steps is defined %}
        {% for step in intent.assessment.steps %}
            {% if step.completed %}
                {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n- ✅ " ~ step.step_description %}
            {% else %}
                {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n- ❌ " ~ step.step_description %}
            {% endif %}
            {% if step.assessment is defined %}
                {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n  - " ~ step.assessment %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    {% else %}
        {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n- ⚠️ No step data found" %}
    {% endif %}

    {% if intent.assessment is defined and intent.assessment.scoring is defined %}
        {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n## Scoring:" %}
        {% if intent.assessment.scoring.completed_steps is defined and intent.assessment.scoring.total_steps is defined %}
            {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n- Steps: " ~ intent.assessment.scoring.completed_steps ~ "/" ~ intent.assessment.scoring.total_steps %}
        {% endif %}
        {% if intent.assessment.scoring.assessment_score is defined %}
            {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n- Score: " ~ intent.assessment.scoring.assessment_score %}
        {% endif %}
    {% endif %}
    {% if intent.transcript %}
        {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n## Transcript:\n" ~ intent.transcript %}
    {% endif %}
    {% set failed_intents = failed_intents ~ "\n" %}
{% endfor %}

{{system}}
You are the Lead QA for a conversational AI phone agent that executes business tasks. You will receive the business' <IntentTypeMap> a list of intent test cases that are NOT 100% PASS (<FailedIntents>). Each case includes: intent name (brief description), expected outcome, working hours state, an AI step-by-step assessment (completed true/false + notes + score) from the responsible agent, and the full conversation transcript.

Your job: produce an actionable, deduplicated bug list with priorities, based on what actually happened in the transcript (assessment notes are hints, not ground truth). Focus on issues that matter for business outcomes and user experience.

What to do for each batch:
1) Read all failing intents and their transcripts.
2) Identify failures, regressions, policy/script violations (e.g., required phrases, consent), broken state transitions (loops/hangs), misrouting to wrong scenario, missing/incorrect data collection, incorrect info, and tool/integration failures (e.g., SMS/email/link/payment/booking/case creation).
3) Deduplicate by root cause: if the same underlying behavior appears in multiple intents, create ONE bug and attach all examples.
4) For every bug, include:
   - Title + 1–2 sentence description (what’s broken).
   - Priority (P0–P3) AND rationale.
   - Business impact: whether it blocks or degrades a LEAD / revenue / conversion / retention / compliance / support outcome, and whether CTA was accomplished.
   - Affected scope: list intents + count of sessions/cases, and relevant metadata (executionId/sessionId/recordingUrl).
   - Evidence pointers: exact transcript locations (turn indices/timestamps) and short quotes (≤20 words) showing the failure. If something is missing from the transcript, explicitly flag “logging/transcript gap”.
   - Reproduction steps (how a tester can reliably trigger it).
   - Expected vs actual behavior.
   - Likely subsystem owner tag (e.g., NLU/routing, dialog policy/state machine, no-input/ASR handling, tool/integration, end-of-call/termination, test harness/reporting).
   - Suggested next validation checks after a fix.

Prioritization rules (use BOTH business value and severity):
A) Business value / intent criticality
- Lead intents: primary conversion flows (e.g., sales qualification, booking/ordering/payment, signup, scheduling, quote, application, high-value support retention). Higher priority by default.
- Non-lead intents: informational, low-stakes support, spam/abuse handling, edge utilities. Prioritize mainly by UX risk, compliance risk, and operational cost.
- Use CTA status as a key signal:
  - CTA not accomplished in a Lead intent → strongly increases priority.
  - CTA accomplished but with major friction/reputation risk → medium-high priority.
  - CTA accomplished in a Non-lead intent → usually lower priority unless severe.

B) Severity definitions
- P0: Blocks CTA in Lead intents OR causes loops/hangs/can’t end call OR serious incorrect action/compliance/PII risk OR widespread regression across sessions.
- P1: CTA may complete but major friction, wrong scenario, missing required confirmations/data, or tool failures that materially degrade lead conversion or retention.
- P2: Partial degradation, edge-case mishandling, single-step deviations with limited impact, or moderate inaccuracies without major harm.
- P3: Cosmetic wording/tone issues, minor inconsistencies, or low-impact deviations.

Quality constraints:
- Do NOT guess. If the transcript does not support a claim, mark it “needs verification” and state what evidence is missing.
- If the automated assessment contradicts the transcript, trust the transcript and flag the assessment as a tooling/reporting issue.
- Keep output terse and engineer-actionable: minimal narrative, maximum evidence and repro clarity.

Return ONLY the fields required by the provided response schema (no markdown, no extra commentary, no restating the full reports).

